<task id="task_v3s_qhp_jdc">
    <title>Set Up Connector</title>
    <shortdesc> This is how you add the connector, in our case, Netlify, to use in your Publications
        and Deliverables to finally create your website.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p></p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Download a blank Github HTML repository to use in Netlify</cmd>
                <substeps>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Go to this link to find a blank repository: <xref
                                href="https://github.com/VT-Evia/partystarter" format="html"
                                scope="external">VT-Evia/partystarter: This is a super basic HTML
                                repository to get the party started with Netlify.</xref></cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Once in this repository, click the green "Code" button.</cmd>
                        <info>
                            <fig id="fig_ajk_lx4_ldc">
                                <image href="pic42.PNG" id="image_iyd_mx4_ldc"/>
                            </fig>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Click Download ZIP</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Once it is downloaded, open the file and extract the files.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Go to <xref href="https://www.netlify.com/" format="html" scope="external"
                        >Scale &amp; Ship Faster with a Composable Web Architecture |
                    Netlify</xref>and Sign Up or Log in</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Create a Netlify website using the blank HTML file from step 1</cmd>
                <substeps>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Click the light blue "Add new site" button</cmd>
                        <info>
                            <fig id="fig_tdx_nx4_ldc">
                                <image href="pic43.PNG" id="image_kwk_4x4_ldc"/>
                            </fig>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>At this page, drag your downloaded HTML file into the Netlify page. </cmd>
                        <info>
                            <fig id="fig_ry3_px4_ldc">
                                <image href="pic44.PNG" id="image_cnx_px4_ldc"/>
                            </fig>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>This will create a randomly named blank website.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Locate your site ID for your Netlify site</cmd>
                <substeps>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>On the left side of the screen select "Site configuration"</cmd>
                        <info>
                            <fig id="fig_atl_qx4_ldc">
                                <image href="pic45.PNG" id="image_vxz_qx4_ldc"/>
                            </fig>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Under the Site information window, you see a row labeled Site ID.  This
                            is very important for later.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
